items.name: LucidWiki
items.title: LucidWiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Lucid Wiki
items.desc: A lucid dream is a dream in which the dreamer is aware that he is dreaming. The dream usually becomes more vivid and memorable. Through controlling the dream, the dreamer can do anything possible, and most things impossible. The Lucid Wiki serves to summarise the vast amount of information in the world about lucid dreaming for your browsing pleasure.

items.name: Nights into Dreams Wiki
items.title: Nights into Dreams Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Nights Wiki!
items.desc: NiGHTS into Dreams (or Nights into Dreams), is a video game released by Sega in 1996 for the Sega Saturn video game system. The game's story follows two children entering a dream world, where they are aided by a being called NiGHTS. This Wiki focuses on the the games and the characters of the NiGHTS universe, please contribute if you have something to add!

items.name: The Little Mermaid
items.title: The Little Mermaid
items.headline: The Little Mermaid Wikia
items.desc: Welcome to The Little Mermaid Wikia! The Little Mermaid Wikia is a free, public and collaborative encyclopedia for everything related to The Little Mermaid saga, the television series, and merchandise. The wiki format allows anyone with a username to create or edit any article, so we can all work together to create a comprehensive database for Little Mermaid fans. Enter now to learn more!

items.name: Metroid Wiki
items.title: Metroid Wiki
items.headline: Scopri di più sulla Metroid Wiki!
items.desc: L'enciclopedia sull'Universo della serie videoludica fantascientifica Metroid. In espansione su tutti i personaggi, i capitoli della saga (compresa la serie a fumetti), l'Universo ramificato in sottocategorie, le armi e le tecnologie, i veicoli, il bestiario, la lista dei boss e infine la colonna sonora.

items.name: Sinjid Wiki
items.title: Sinjid Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Sinjid Wikia
items.desc:
Sinjid is a series of role-playing action-adventure flash games created by Krin and published through Armor Games. It revolves around a character of the same name.
There are three games in the Sinjid series up to now: Sinjid Battle Arena, Sinjid Shadow of the Warrior and Sinjid. Although they are not technically sequels and posess conflicting plots, each of them have some elements in common with each other, like the main character, which is Sinjid himself, a battle system with equipment, equipment upgrades, level system, skill system, and more. All of them thematically, and in the case of "Sinjid" explicitly, take place in a version of Feudal Japan where magic and monsters exist.

items.name: Vocaloid Wiki
items.title: Vocaloid Wiki
items.headline: Bienvenido al mundo Vocaloid
items.desc:
Wiki Vocaloid es un proyecto desarrollado en torno al software Vocaloid de Yamaha.co, un programa sintetizador de voz el cual permite desarrollar diálogos o canciones a partir de diferentes bancos de voz. 

A la fecha existen 3 versiones del motor vocaloid, y mas de 40 bancos de voz diferentes los que incluyen idiomas tales como Inglés, Japonés, Coreano, Chino y Español. 

Entre los voicebanks mas conocidos encontramos los de la empresas 
* Crypton co. KAITO, MEIKO, Hatsune Miku, Kagamine Rin y Len, Megurine Luka.  
* Internet co. Gakupo, Megpoid, Lily, Gachapoid, CUL

items.name: My Bride is a Mermaid Wiki
items.title: My Bride is a Mermaid Wiki
items.headline: My Bride is a Mermaid Wiki
items.desc: My Bride is a Mermaid Wiki is a free online resource for information about the Seto no Hanayome anime and manga series, distributed in english as "My Bride is a Mermaid".  The manga series was written by Tahiko Kimura and serialized between the September 2002 and May 2009 issues of Monthly Gangan Wing, and the June and December 2010 issues of Monthly Gangan Joker, both published by Square Enix. A 26-episode anime television series adaptation animated by Gonzo and directed by Seiji Kishi aired in Japan on TV Tokyo between April and September 2007. Two original video animation episodes were released in November 2008 and January 2009.

items.desc: EverymanHYBRID is an online transmedia story that began as an amateur YouTube fitness series in March 2010. The series features three guys in their 20s named Vincent, Evan, and Jeff. A familiar entity may be found lingering in the videos as a horrific easter-egg: the tall, eldritch Slenderman. What at first seemed a contrived "Slenderman rip-off series" spiraled, looped and flashed back to become something much, much worse; something truly awful. Join our wiki to find out more.

items.name: Vocaloid Wiki
items.title: Vocaloid Wiki
items.headline: Willkommen im Vocaloid Wiki
items.desc:
VOCALOID, VOCALOID2 und VOCALOID3 sind Software Synthesizer, mit denen es möglich ist, auf Grundlage echter Stimmen, künstlichen Gesang zu erzeugen.

Desweiteren existieren auch verschiedene Spiele für die PS3, PSVita, PSP und für den Computer.

Es gibt sogar spezielle Musiker, Alben, Figuren und sogar ganze Konzerte des Programmes!

Es gibt eine Menge verschiedener Vocaloids, wie z.B. Kaito, Hatsune Miku, Kamui Gakupo und SF-A2 Miki, die in Japanisch singen oder Vocaloids, wie Lola, Big Al und Miriam, die in Englisch singen. Es gibt auch einige wenige mit einer chinesischen oder koreanischen Voicebanks, aber leider gibt es bisher keine deutschen Vocaloids. Allerdings existieren im Internet einige gute Covers von echten Sängern aber auch von deutschen UTAUloids, um sich die geliebten Lieder von Miku, Luka und Co. auch übersetzt anhören zu können.

Vocaloid et UTAU sont des logiciels de musique assistée par ordinateur qui permettent de synthétiser les voix humaines. Les logiciels proposent diverses chanteuses et chanteuses virtuels, qui sont parfois des icônes, comme Hatsune Miku (Vocaloid) qui donne des concerts et a eu droit à plusieurs jeux vidéo et produits dérivés.

items.name: Danceroid Wiki
items.title: Danceroid Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Danceroid Wiki!
items.desc:
Danceroid Wiki is about a Japanese Dance Group. They started in 2009, as a trio, by uploading a video to Japanese Website, Nico Nico Douga for their anual contest, Odetta-mita (I Tried This Dance).
Still active, the group went from a trio, to a pentet (5), then to a Quartet (4), and now to a Septet (7)! It's hard to believe that a Trio of three friends became a group a seven girls that have fans all around the Globe.
